ai-patthana16.11:0.2_0: Having given the immaculateness of the Dhamma
ai-patthana16.11:0.3_0: looking forwards and looking around on,
ai-patthana16.11:1.1_0: Not looking on an incompetent teaching, not with no reason.
ai-patthana16.11:1.1_1: Not looking at the next world, he doesn’t give rise to the thought, nor is there a reason for the sake of excessive conditions.
ai-patthana16.11:1.1_2: Not looking at the next world, he doesn’t give rise to the thought, nor is there a reason for the sake of excessive conditions.
ai-patthana16.11:1.1_3: Thoughts that are independent of this world don’t arise because of reason, and if they don’t arise.
ai-patthana16.11:1.1_4: Thoughts that are indeed unprofitable and independent, and skilled in reasons. Their conditions don’t arise because of this.
ai-patthana16.11:1.1_7: the five hindrances are not clear.
ai-patthana16.11:2.1_0: A skillful quality doesn’t give rise to yearning for the north, or outcome.
ai-patthana16.11:2.1_1: A skillful quality doesn’t give rise to yearning for the sake of a skillful, nor an upper robe.
ai-patthana16.11:2.1_2: A skillful person doesn’t give rise to skillful qualities, or supramundane Dhamma. They don’t give rise to yet.
ai-patthana16.11:3.1_0: Not incomparable by this world, no cause or condition.
ai-patthana16.11:3.1_1: Not incomparable by this world, no cause or condition.
ai-patthana16.11:3.1_2: unsurpassed in this way, incomparable, or with the supermundane and the supermundane do not arise.
ai-patthana16.11:3.1_3: This is the section in brief.
